From 3cebb430284a4066204409a02821caba8d08061f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: sarabjeets <sarabjeets@marvell.com>
Date: Thu, 21 Aug 2025 14:45:53 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] [SONICDC-498] pc/test_lag_member_forwarding fails with BFD
 offload capability query failed

The BFD offload capability is optional for the product, so changing the log level from ERROR to WARNING.
Hence changed BFD offload capability Log Level to WARN Instead of error.

Signed-off-by: sarabjeets <sarabjeets@marvell.com>
---
 orchagent/bfdorch.cpp | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/orchagent/bfdorch.cpp b/orchagent/bfdorch.cpp
index c9b672b7..c37b178a 100644
--- a/orchagent/bfdorch.cpp
+++ b/orchagent/bfdorch.cpp
@@ -745,7 +745,7 @@ bool BgpGlobalStateOrch::offload_supported(bool get_ipv6)
                                             attr.id, &capability);
     if (status != SAI_STATUS_SUCCESS)
     {
-        SWSS_LOG_ERROR("Unable to query BFD offload capability");
+        SWSS_LOG_WARN("Unable to query BFD offload capability");
         return false;
     }
     if (!capability.get_implemented)
-- 
2.25.1

